value.value: Adult ascending neuron that does not arborize in the ventral nerve cord (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a primary neuron of the 27X hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It exits the VNC via the cervical connective (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the brain and sends output to the brain (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 4 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the mesothoracic neuromere and prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
